01:16.107 --> 01:19.275
You have something
to say to me?

01:19.343 --> 01:21.344
I'm sorry, Scottie.

01:21.412 --> 01:24.314
I didn't believe you,
but you were telling the truth.

01:25.716 --> 01:27.384
Why does it always
have to be so--

01:27.451 --> 01:28.918
- I said I was sorry.
- You didn't mean it.

01:28.986 --> 01:30.286
I meant it.

01:30.354 --> 01:32.022
But just because I was wrong
about you betraying me

01:32.089 --> 01:34.257
doesn't mean I was wrong
to think you might have done it.

01:34.325 --> 01:35.792
See, this is what I mean,
Harvey.

01:35.860 --> 01:38.261
If you thought anything of me,
you'd know I'd never do that.

01:38.329 --> 01:39.629
I do think something
of you,

01:39.697 --> 01:41.731
which is why I'm going to
tell you this: Get out.

01:41.799 --> 01:43.933
Honor the dissolution agreement
and move on.

01:44.001 --> 01:45.635
You've got to be
kidding me.

01:45.703 --> 01:48.505
You want me to put
all the liability on Edward?

01:48.572 --> 01:50.173
The liability
belongs on Edward.

01:50.241 --> 01:51.775
So when you say that you think
something of me,

01:51.842 --> 01:53.376
what you actually mean is
you want me to help you

01:53.444 --> 01:54.878
to bail
on Darby International.

01:54.945 --> 01:56.346
Scottie,
when this lawsuit's over,

01:56.414 --> 01:57.614
there's not going to be
a Darby International.

01:57.681 --> 01:59.215
- You don't know that.
- What I know is

01:59.283 --> 02:00.850
you have a chance
to get another job

02:00.918 --> 02:03.420
before everything hits the fan.
You won't in another week.

02:03.487 --> 02:05.255
I won't need another job
when I right the ship.

02:05.322 --> 02:07.123
You're not going to right
the ship.

02:07.191 --> 02:09.859
If you were on that jury,
the only question you'd ask

02:09.926 --> 02:12.762
is how many zeroes
to put on the check.

02:16.117 --> 02:18.168
You want me to turn my back
on the man

02:18.235 --> 02:21.571
that I've been in the foxhole
with for the last ten years.

02:21.639 --> 02:23.206
Would you do the same?

02:23.274 --> 02:25.308
If that man turned out
to have sanctioned murder

02:25.359 --> 02:28.211
without my knowledge and let me
take the hit, I would.

02:32.450 --> 02:35.651
Hmm.

02:35.703 --> 02:39.622
Well...like it or not,
you're in the foxhole with me.

02:39.690 --> 02:42.409
So order a glass
of your Macallan 20-pretentious,

02:42.493 --> 02:45.328
and let's figure out how we're
going to fight this together.

02:51.936 --> 02:53.903
You haven't said a word
all night.

02:53.971 --> 02:55.305
Are we going to talk
about this or not?

02:55.372 --> 02:56.806
What is there
to talk about?

02:56.857 --> 02:58.297
This is why you didn't want
to decide

02:58.308 --> 03:00.076
whether to live with me
or not, right?

03:00.144 --> 03:01.644
Well, it isn't,
actually,

03:01.712 --> 03:03.680
but you knew that I was
applying to Stanford,

03:03.747 --> 03:05.448
and you said that you'd support
whatever decision I made.

03:05.516 --> 03:08.218
I did, but then
you got into Columbia,

03:08.285 --> 03:10.587
so I thought
that wouldn't matter anymore.

03:10.638 --> 03:12.172
Because Stanford's
in California,

03:12.256 --> 03:14.257
and Columbia's here.
And because Columbia

03:14.325 --> 03:16.509
is an amazing school
and we said we love each other.

03:16.594 --> 03:18.061
Yeah, but it's not
that simple.

03:18.129 --> 03:20.997
It sounds that simple to me.

03:22.683 --> 03:26.586
[Stutters]
What I mean is

03:26.670 --> 03:28.404
I'm not built
the same as you.

03:28.472 --> 03:30.707
I need to decide
what school is better for me

03:30.774 --> 03:33.276
before factoring in you or us
or anything else.

03:33.344 --> 03:34.761
And how exactly
do you plan on doing that?

03:34.845 --> 03:36.713
The same way that I make
all the important decisions

03:36.780 --> 03:39.165
in my life,
by weighing the pros and cons

03:39.250 --> 03:40.583
of both schools.

03:40.651 --> 03:42.885
And where does not being
with me rank on that list?

03:42.937 --> 03:44.504
You're missing the point.

03:44.588 --> 03:46.556
I am trying to figure out
which school is best for me

03:46.623 --> 03:48.424
in a vacuum.
No, you're missing the point.

03:48.476 --> 03:50.426
You're trying to figure out
what school is best for you

03:50.478 --> 03:52.261
as though I didn't exist,
but I do.

03:52.313 --> 03:54.030
- Mike--
- Rachel, I'm not saying

03:54.081 --> 03:56.399
that you have to
go to Columbia.

03:56.467 --> 03:59.836
We're adults.
We're together.

03:59.904 --> 04:02.605
At some point, you're going to
have to factor that in too.

04:02.656 --> 04:03.873
[Door closes]

04:06.043 --> 04:08.928
- She go for it?
- No, she didn't.

04:09.013 --> 04:10.914
Then if Scottie won't
separate from us amicably,

04:10.981 --> 04:12.282
we'll make her do it
forcibly.

04:12.349 --> 04:14.150
Jessica, I don't want to start
another war with her.

04:14.218 --> 04:15.658
- Then what's your idea?
- My idea is

04:15.719 --> 04:17.921
we act like lawyers
and we fight the lawsuit.

04:17.988 --> 04:19.755
On its merits?

04:19.822 --> 04:22.892
Edward Darby sanctioned murder.
We don't stand a chance.

04:22.943 --> 04:26.095
- Jessica--
- Harvey, you know I'm right,

04:26.163 --> 04:28.214
and it's what you told
Scottie--

04:28.299 --> 04:30.600
it's the truth, and just because
she can't see it

04:30.668 --> 04:31.651
doesn't mean
we have to live with it.

04:31.735 --> 04:32.835
No, we don't.

04:32.903 --> 04:34.303
I need you to get in a room
with Ava

04:34.305 --> 04:36.306
and offer our testimony
against Edward

04:36.373 --> 04:39.192
in exchange for taking our names
off the lawsuit.

04:40.644 --> 04:43.513
What about when Scottie
finds out?

04:51.055 --> 04:52.939
Thanks.

05:03.194 --> 05:04.662
11:08.

05:04.713 --> 05:06.664
For being late
to a settlement conference.

05:06.731 --> 05:08.766
Tanner, what the hell are you
doing here, and how the hell

05:08.833 --> 05:10.851
did you insinuate yourself
with Ava Hessington?

05:10.936 --> 05:12.603
- Jealous?
- No, I just thought Hessington

05:12.671 --> 05:15.406
was in the oil business,
not the snake oil business.

05:15.474 --> 05:16.974
Ha ha.
They diversified.

05:17.042 --> 05:19.877
- Where's Ava?
- Ava's not here,

05:19.928 --> 05:21.479
because she's not interested
in your offer

05:21.546 --> 05:22.980
to testify
against Edward Darby.

05:23.031 --> 05:24.431
I'm not the one
who did this to her.

05:24.449 --> 05:26.517
Aren't you? Didn't you pull
your typical bullshit

05:26.585 --> 05:28.202
to get the original attorney
thrown off this case?

05:28.286 --> 05:30.254
- To win the damn case.
- Well, instead of winning it,

05:30.322 --> 05:31.622
it led to Ava being charged
with murder.

05:31.690 --> 05:33.023
A charge I got her off of

05:33.091 --> 05:35.059
by finding the people
who were actually responsible.

05:35.126 --> 05:36.527
Sorry, Harv,
but that's not enough,

05:36.595 --> 05:38.863
and Ava has no intention
of letting you off the hook.

05:38.930 --> 05:41.148
Ava or you?

05:41.233 --> 05:42.933
We both know
you tracked her down

05:42.984 --> 05:44.952
because of your lifelong,
never-gonna-happen dream

05:45.036 --> 05:46.287
to beat me.
I never heard

05:46.371 --> 05:48.122
of Ava Hessington until
she walked through my door.

05:48.206 --> 05:50.040
Bullshit.
You have a subscription

05:50.108 --> 05:51.825
to Harvey Specter monthly,
and I know it.

05:51.910 --> 05:53.661
[Laughing]
Okay, you got me.

05:53.745 --> 05:54.879
I knew exactly who she was

05:54.946 --> 05:56.413
the second she walked
through my door--

05:56.464 --> 05:58.382
my chance to take
your lunch money.

05:58.449 --> 06:01.919
Well, let me make you
an advance payment.

06:01.970 --> 06:04.288
[Coin clattering]
Why don't you use this

06:04.339 --> 06:06.423
to call your mom and tell her
to get the tissues ready,

06:06.474 --> 06:08.175
because you're 0-2
against me,

06:08.260 --> 06:11.862
and the 0 isn't the number
that's going to change.

06:11.930 --> 06:15.566
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:15.633 --> 06:18.903
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:18.970 --> 06:22.072
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:22.140 --> 06:25.809
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:25.860 --> 06:28.746
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

06:28.813 --> 06:32.750
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

